item.title: Scary is an understatement. Reposting w/ added context
item.description:
https://www.dexerto.com/entertainment/meta-patents-ai-that-takes-over-a-dead-persons-account-to-keep-posting-and-chatting-3320326/
So we all knew they were stealing our data, but ...
2023 you say?
It's gone from an egregious breach of privacy and identity by meta (yet again) to a horrendous manipulation of society and reality as we know it. The implications are astronomical and should not be brushed aside. The amount of bots I encounter casually browsing my corners of the internet are spreading like an infection.
Soon humans will be a small minority in the online sphere, especially when quantum computing is inevitably involved. The US seems to be a major pushing factor in this shift. Where will we go when it's too congested to reach each other? When they rewrite reality to show whatever prompt of their choosing? Is it already happening?

item.title: The Dutch have the best sports color
item.description: Orange is the historic national colour of the Netherlands, originating from one of the many title of the ruling head of state, Prince of Orange. The founder of the House of Orange, William the Silent, is like the Dutch George Washington. If George Washington had followed up his victory over the British by producing a whole line of Washington's with a fair number of them being military or political geniuses in their own right. Who repeatedly stood up, and at times gave their life, to save the nation at its most dire moments: Maurice of Orange (military genius), Frederick Henry of Orange (nicknamed 'the city breaker' for his skill at seiging), William III of Orange (successfully invaded and took over England), Wilhelmina Queen of the Netherlands (the icon of Dutch resistance against the Nazi occupation). And those are just the most illustrious, there's even more who weren't geniuses but did do their part in their time (and for the record, there were a few rotten apples too of course). Basically, unlike many of the European royal families which were often just imported from Germany when the native line died out coughenglandcough ;D, the House of Orange has been intimately tied with the history and fortunes of the Netherlands since our beginnings as an independent nation. https://old.reddit.com/r/olympics/comments/1y4e2l/why_do_we_always_see_the_dutch_in_the_color/cfhgj77/

item.title: (Nearly) finished my Terra Cosplay
item.description:
After wearing it completely for the first time I have some things that I want to change improve f.e. More details on the cape, need to make her earrings and I’m not happy with the belt situation!
It all started with a bag of fabrics and my favourite pattern
First try on of the basic dress - it was too long and to big
Took me forever to decide which trim I want to use at the end of the dress - ended up with the gold pink combo!
Glued on the embroidery while wearing the dress bc it would not have fit if I just sewed it on while laying flat on the floor, after the glue dried I also sewed them down
Started with the sleeve details and couldn’t stop!
The sleeves turned out to be my favourite part of the cosplay!
Dyed the fabric for the cape
Had to paint the stockings while wearing them
First try on with the bedazzled dress and sleeves ?
Super happy when we found another Terra and Celes at Kupocon ??

item.title: Bride surprises wedding guests with stem cell donor who saved her life
item.description: Kaedi Cecala revealed the man whose selfless act gave her a second chance at life was among the wedding guests. A bride left wedding guests stunned and many in tears after revealing that the stem cell donor who saved her life was standing among them. Kaedi Cecala was diagnosed with myelodysplastic syndrome, a rare blood cancer, in 2020. After an aggressive chemotherapy regimen, doctors found a perfect match in Karol Zwierzyski, a 26-year-old living in Poland. The transplant was a success, and Kaedi is now cancer-free. At her wedding, Kaedi surprised guests by introducing Zwierzyski, who traveled from Poland to attend the celebration. Source: https://nationaltoday.com/us/il/chicago/news/2026/02/17/bride-surprises-wedding-guests-with-stem-cell-donor-who-saved-her-life/
